THE VISUAL IMAGE' ITS IMMEDIACY AND TRADITION.
     
THE HILL MONASTIC MANUSCRIPT MICROFILM LIBRARY, SAINT JOHN'S UNIVERSITY,
MINNESOTA, WAS FOUNDED IN 1964, AND HAS BEEN ENGAGED IN MICROFILMING THE
ENTIRE MANUSCRIPT COLLECTIONS STILL EXTANT IN EUROPEAN MONASTIC AND ALLIED
LIBRARIES. DESCRIBES THE PROJECT, CATALOGUING PRACTICE, AND INCLUDES EXAMPLES
OF MAIN CATALOGUE ENTRIES.
